data.entity_name: Gaussian Ellipse Parameterization for Fixed Components (equation)
data.content: This equation calculates the mean and standard deviation parameters for a 2D Gaussian distribution to generate semantic heatmaps for fixed components. By defining the elliptical spread based on bounding box dimensions, it enables precise spatial representation of object locations and uncertainty in multi-channel semantic images. Critical for target detection in engineering applications, it connects probabilistic modeling with computer vision frameworks for industrial analysis.

data.entity_name: Gaussian Ellipse Coordinate Range for Semantic Image (equation)
data.content: Defines the spatial extent of pixel coordinates in a semantic image based on a 3σ interval of a bivariate normal distribution. Captures probabilistic spatial relationships for target localization in FFTNet, enabling precise regression of fixed component positions and scales through Gaussian ellipse construction.

data.entity_name: Semantic Range Definition for Gaussian Heatmaps (equation)
